---
---
<section id="awards" class="max-w-[1100px] mx-auto px-10 pb-24">
  <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-12">
    <span class="font-mono text-[11px] text-accent uppercase tracking-[0.1em]">
      <span data-lang="en">Awards</span>
      <span data-lang="de">Auszeichnungen</span>
    </span>
    <div class="flex-1 h-px bg-border"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[80px_1fr] gap-6 py-8 border-t border-border border-b">
    <div class="font-mono text-xs text-muted pt-1">2021</div>
    <div>
      <div class="font-mono text-[10px] text-accent uppercase tracking-[0.1em] mb-2 flex items-center gap-1.5">
        <span>★</span>
        <span data-lang="en">1st Place</span>
        <span data-lang="de">1. Platz</span>
      </div>
      <div class="font-serif text-xl font-normal tracking-[-0.01em] leading-snug mb-2">
        Digital Science Week Science Slam
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">
        <span data-lang="en">
          Won with Thorben Schomacker for <em>"AI Methods as Censorship Tools"</em> — examining
          AI methods for detecting computational propaganda. Also built an interactive chatbot
          enabling 200+ participants to test conspiracy detection live on Telegram. Hosted by
          Network of Labs · Universität Hamburg.{' '}
          <a
            href="https://www.inf.uni-hamburg.de/inst/basecamp/blog/21-02-15-digital-science-week-2021.html"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-accent hover:underline"
            aria-label="Digital Science Week 2021 blog post (opens in new tab)"
          >
            Read more ↗
          </a>
        </span>
        <span data-lang="de">
          Gewonnen mit Thorben Schomacker für <em>„KI-Methoden als Zensurmaßnahme"</em> —
          Untersuchung von KI-Methoden zur Erkennung von Computational Propaganda. Zudem
          einen interaktiven Chatbot entwickelt, mit dem 200+ Teilnehmende die
          Verschwörungstheorie-Erkennung live auf Telegram testen konnten.
          Veranstaltet vom Network of Labs · Universität Hamburg.{' '}
          <a
            href="https://www.inf.uni-hamburg.de/inst/basecamp/blog/21-02-15-digital-science-week-2021.html"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-accent hover:underline"
            aria-label="Digital Science Week 2021 Blogeintrag (öffnet in neuem Tab)"
          >
            Mehr lesen ↗
          </a>
        </span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
